nctional","section":"FPS Payment Flow","title":"Settlement Result Notification to Payer Bank (Step 5a)","description":"The payer bank receives the settlement result from HKICL (transmission format: FIToFIPmtStsRpt (pacs.002)) and notifies the payer of the transfer result.","business_rules":["Transmission format must be pacs.002 (FIToFIPmtStsRpt)"],"acceptance_criteria":["Payer bank receives pacs.002 message from HKICL as settlement result","Payer bank notifies the payer of the transfer result"],"dependencies":["Settlement Execution by HKICL FPS Platform"],"testability":true,"source_type":"web"},{"page":"2","page_number":2,"requirement_type":"Functional","section":"FPS Payment Flow","title":"Settlement Result Notification to Beneficiary Bank (Step 5b)","description":"The beneficiary bank receives the settlement result from HKICL (transmission format: FIToFIPmtStsRpt (pacs.002)).","business_rules":["Transmission format must be pacs.002 (FIToFIPmtStsRpt)"],"acceptance_criteria":["Beneficiary bank receives pacs.002 message from HKICL as settlement result"],"dependencies":["Settlement Execution by HKICL FPS Platform"],"testability":true,"source_type":"web"},{"page":"2","page_number":2,"requirement_type":"Functional","section":"FPS Payment Flow","title":"Credit Notification to Payer","description":"The system informs the payer of the credit result to the beneficiary account.","business_rules":[],"acceptance_criteria":["Payer is notified of the credit result to the beneficiary account"],"dependencies":["Settlement Result Notification to Payer Bank (Step 5a)"],"testability":true,"source_type":"web"},{"page":"2","page_number":2,"requirement_type":"Functional","section":"Message Reference","title":"Message Type Reference Table","description":"A reference table listing message types, names, and layout sections for Real-time and Batch scenarios, including pacs.008 Credit Transfer, pacs.008 Account Verification, pacs.002 Account Verification Result, and pacs.002 Payment Status Report.","business_rules":["Message pacs.008 Credit Transfer uses layout 3.5.1 / Sc.A for both Real-time and Batch","Message pacs.008 Account Verification uses layout 3.5.1 / Sc.B for Real-time only","Message pacs.002 Account Verification Result uses layout 3.5.2 / Sc.E for Real-time only","Message pacs.002 Payment Status Report (5a) uses layout 3.5.2 / Sc.A for Real-time and 3.5.2 / Sc.B for Batch","Message pacs.002 Payment Status Report (5b) uses layout 3.5.2 / Sc.C for Real-time only"],"acceptance_criteria":["Each message type conforms to the specified layout and scenario as per the reference table"],"dependencies":[],"testability":true,"source_type":"web"}]
Additional Web decomposition guardrail:
- Do not split modules only by wording variants, display labels, input value categories, or channel/context labels when they describe the same executable test intent.
- Keep one submodule and describe supported variants/contexts in `description` only when the page state, primary user action, validation rules, actor responsibility, and business outcome are still the same.
- Do split when the document shows a different primary action or entry point on the same page, such as upload, download, submit, confirm, navigate to next step, open details, trigger validation, or any other independently testable control.
- Do split when the document shows a different UI/page state, different required fields, different validation rules, different actor/system responsibility, different business stage, or materially different downstream outcome.
- Do not merge page entry/access check logic with subsequent in-page action controls when they are separately testable.
- Do not merge static display/content areas with actionable controls when the controls trigger their own flow or system behavior.
- Coverage comes first: if unsure whether two items are the same executable test intent, keep them as separate submodules with concise names.
